        <headline>Flood Advisory issued May 27 at 5:57PM EDT until May 27 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast South Carolina, including the
following counties, Berkeley, Charleston and Dorchester.

* WHEN...Until 630 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Water over roadways. Overflowing poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 556 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated showers and
thunderstorms with torrential rainfall extending from
Summerville and Cooke Crossroads east to Goose Creek. These
storms are slow moving and have already dropped as much as 1
to 3 inches of rain. An additional inch could fall through
630 PM, resulting in minor flooding of urban and poor
drainage areas.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
North Charleston, Summerville, Goose Creek, Hanahan, Ladson,
Naval Weapons Station Charleston, Crowfield Plantation,
College Park, Sangaree and Lincolnville.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
